    <h1>Managing feedbacks</h1><div id="preamble">
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="admonitionblock important">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-important" title="Important"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Note about the Managing feedbacks page of the manual</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>This page of the manual describes all settings that are available in the <strong>CRM » Feedback ratings</strong> menu in the Terra back end using the centralised login. The <a href="/en/omni-channel/online-store/setting-up-clients/extras/customer-feedback">Customer feedback</a> page of the manual and the <a href="/en/omni-channel/online-store/setting-up-clients/cms#customer-feedback">Customer feedback</a> chapter that describe the settings in the <strong>CMS » Customer feedback</strong> and <strong>Setup » Client » Settings » Feedback</strong> menus will be simultaneously available. Once the new <strong>CMS » Feedback ratings</strong> menu has completely replaced the old <strong>CMS » Customer feedback</strong> menu, the <strong>CMS » Customer feedback</strong> menu as well as the <strong>Customer feedback</strong> page of the manual will be removed.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p><a href="https://marketplace.plentymarkets.com/en/plugins/widgets/Feedback_5115" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Customer feedback</a> is a plugin for the <a href="https://marketplace.plentymarkets.com/en/plugins/templates/Ceres_4697" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Ceres</a> online store. Install this plugin to display customer reviews in the online store and reply to feedbacks. Release reviews submitted by your customers in the <strong>CMS » Feedback ratings</strong> menu. In this menu, you also reply to customer feedbacks or edit them. It is also possible to migrate existing customer reviews or delete reviews in this menu.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="100">1. Migrating customer reviews</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>When switching from your old Callisto online store to the new Ceres online store, your existing customer reviews will also be available in Ceres after migrating them. To migrate existing customer reviews, proceed as follows.</p>
</div>
<div id="200" class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Migrating existing customer reviews:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>CMS » Feedback ratings</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Migrate existing feedbacks</strong>.<br>
→ The existing feedbacks will be migrated.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock note">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-note" title="Note"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Migration of existing customer reviews</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>During the migration process, existing customer reviews will be transferred to the new data base structure. Customer reviews will have a maximum rating of 5 in the new structure. Customer reviews using a rating scale of 10 rating points, will be converted into a maximum of 5 rating points when migrating:</p>
</div>
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li>
<p>1 to 2 stars will be converted into 1 star</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>3 to 4 stars will be converted into 2 stars</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>5 to 6 stars will be converted into 3 stars</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>7 to 8 stars will be converted into 4 stars</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>9 to 10 stars will be converted into 5 stars</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="300">2. Searching for customer reviews</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In the <strong>Filter</strong> view, you can search for customer reviews according to specific criteria. The search results will be listed in the <strong>Overview</strong> view. The overview currently displays the following information: ID, type, reference ID, title, author, date, comment, rating, replies, visibility. Learn how to edit customer reviews in the <a href="#700">Editing customer reviews</a> chapter.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In order to search for specific customer reviews, enter an ID in the search field or select the appropriate drop-down list settings.</p>
</div>
<div id="400" class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Searching for customer reviews:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>CMS » Feedback ratings</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the <strong>Filter</strong> view, enter the ID in the search field or set the filter options in the drop-down lists. Pay attention to the information given in <a href="#table-filters-customer-reviews">Table 1</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Search</strong>.<br>
→ The customer reviews that correspond to the search criteria entered will be displayed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click in the line of the customer review.<br>
→ The detail view of the customer review will open.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<table id="table-filters-customer-reviews" class="tableblock frame-all grid-all stretch">
